The paper uses machine learning tools to analyze Instagram photos and identify markers of depression. This involves color analysis, metadata components, and algorithmic face detection, which are all related to computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the study involves statistical analysis of large amounts of data, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also touches on the psychological aspects of depression and how it can be detected through social media, which could be categorized under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves the use of computational methods to analyze large amounts of data, which could be categorized under cybernetics (cs.CY).
